    "body": "### Problem\n\nI put a full vertical line as a status symbol (because it's beautiful) and allow me with git signs to see what's added/modified/removed.\nIf I also have a window separator it's also ugly because there spaces betwee the \"│\"\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3aa05800-4801-4fdb-9570-f621eb894e2a)\n\nSo what I do is I have no window separator. It looks great\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7f4a935f-0ab5-4a2b-8d5f-d39cdd14fbf8)\n\n\nBut now if a file has only a few lines it looks bad again (look at two windows in the middle)\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/520a5ca6-dc21-4664-850c-909b99009639)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI want an option such as statussymbolforcefullheight to force status symbol to be 100%\n\nI'm open to other alternatives but there is no AFAIK \"│\" that are right or left aligned. Because if it existed maybe I could do so statusymbol is left aligned and window separator is left or right aligned (depending on position on the window I guess) so status symbol and window separator would merge into one thicker line.\nThat would be perfect but I cannot find unicode symbol left/right aligned and 100% height and vim doesn't provide a way AFAIK to change window separator based on buffer's position.\n\nThere's also other big problems with my method:\n- The intersections of windows: I cannot use the proper intersection unicode character because otherwise it would one column too far left. The reason for that is window separator is invisible, status column acts as a sort of window separator but it's one column to the right.\n- Dragging window is super hard. I have to always click the invisible symbol one column left of status column because it's the real window separator (but invisible).\n\nI wished there was just a way to merge the concept of window separator and status symbol (maybe just apply the color highlight on the window separator itself)",
