            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "To rephrase my original post : I want the clean look of one single bar that separate windows and can have color highlights (here used for git). Two options\n\n### Option 1\nTo achieve that I can carry on using status symbol but multiple points are blocking : we need a statuslineheight, we might want (for better look) to handler corners that are one column off, dragging windows should be made easier (currently it's one column off because window separator is invisible, either we have option to move left status column or we have option to move the area that's draggable).\nSeems a bit much (and require manual configuration of user for statuslineheight, for characters of status symbol etc.)\n\n### Option 2\n\nThe alternative I can think of that would levarage the laststatus=3 code would just add highlights to window separators. It would solve all of the issue above and avoid any kind of manual setup (as laststatus=3 has already all the proper unicode).\n\nAlso we'd need https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/33041to also have no statusline (not strictly required but cleaner UI especially now the issues with noice I think have been fixed on 0.11 statusline is not needed anymore for most cases).\n\nBTW I thought my issue would be disregarded as very minor and niche. I'm glad some core members agree the look looks good and is open to improving the implementation of it :)  ",
